<br>
Honestly, who the heck isn't LFG most times?  I've seen every class thinkable sitting at the zoneline in Valor shouting for a group (up to an hour or more in most cases).  Clerics and Enchanters are the only class that is blessed with never havin to find a group.  Shamans rank right up there for their slows.  Honestly I have few problems finding a group, and when I have problems I find something else to do besides xp'ing.  <br>
<br>
And the soloing issue has been buried for a long time.  Druids and wizards are about the only two classes that never have problems soloing.  Enchanters AND mages can somewhat solo pretty darned well given their 64/65 charms.  Remember that magicians have the most stable charm spell in the game (built in -100 resist adjustment and 20 minute max duration).  Necros are still upset because of the fact they can't fear most planar mobs (the snares don't last long either).  Don't even get started on melee classes (rogues and warriors will NEVER be able to solo 61+).  The fact is, everyone has trouble soloing.  Sure I'd like to be able to solo in my spare time, and there are still ways, but it shouldn't be made any easier--level 61+ shouldn't be easy on anyone because it is the high level game.  But, if Sony tries to nerf the wizard/druid soloing I can promise a lot of feelings will go flying.  <br>
<br>
But if you spend a lot of time LFG, it most likely isn't a fault of the magician class.  We are very well balanced as a class and more than fill our role in a group.  The times I do get in a group of people I don't know it doesn't take long to prove to them exactly how much damage I am capable of adding. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=222062">Booperbustle Tinkermeister</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
